711206f-a.text:
(1) East 14th Street looking West from Avenue C to Avenue B.
November 24, 1918
President Borough Manhattan

717958f-a.text:
Ave. C, north from East 14th Street, showing a gas holder of the Consolidated Gas Co. across the fenced area at the western part of the 14th to 15th Street block. North of same appears the Repair Shops of the City of New York.
June 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

717961f-a.text:
Avenue C, north across East 14th Street. An empty lot occupies the 14th to 15th Street frontage. On the block north is a gas holder of the Consolidated Edison Co. The utilitarian building above (16th to 17th Streets) is the N. Y. C. Motor Transport Building. At this point this avenue terminates and traffic flows into Exterior Street. Eventually the latter will become a portion of the East River Drive.
October 23, 1939
P. L. Sperr
